sql:
SELECT AVG(uptake_value) AS average_uptake
FROM uptake_measurements
WHERE experiment_id = 101;

SELECT AVG(concentration_value) AS average_concentration
FROM concentrations
WHERE concentration_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- The first version of the experiment refers to the experiment with a version number of 1; 
- A plant and treatment in this context refer to a plant and treatment with a specific and unique combination of experiment_id, plant_name, and treatment_name;
- Average uptake values and environmental conditions provide a comprehensive view of an experiment's performance under various conditions.

sql:
SELECT measurement_method, SUM(uptake_value) AS total_uptake
FROM uptake_measurements
GROUP BY measurement_method;
